<Base title="About" description="About Alex Janiak.">
	<h1 class="page-title">About</h1>

	<p><span class="newthought">Hi! I'm Alex Janiak</span>, a startup founder interested in mechanism design, systems engineering, rational decision-making, and the parts of philosophy that start where clean formalism runs out: Nagel, Wittgenstein, post-rationalism, and the subjectivity stuff.</p>

	<p>I am currently building AI forecasting systems to help people make better decisions under uncertainty.</p>

	<section class="about-section">
		<h3>Current</h3>
		<ul class="about-list">
			<li>
				<span class="about-item-detail"><strong>Stealth forecasting company</strong><br />Co-founder, building AI forecasting systems.</span>
				<span class="about-item-title">2025-</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="about-item-detail"><strong>Combinator</strong><br />Co-founder. Built the first general-purpose decision markets platform.</span>
				<span class="about-item-title">2025-</span>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="about-section">
		<h3>Education</h3>
		<ul class="about-list">
			<li>
				<span class="about-item-detail"><strong>Duke University</strong><br />B.S. Computer Science, B.A. Philosophy, Minor in Mathematics.</span>
				<span class="about-item-title">2021-2025</span>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="about-section">
		<h3>Experience</h3>
		<ul class="about-list">
			<li>
				<span class="about-item-detail"><strong>Amazon Web Services (AWS Lambda)</strong><br />Software development engineering intern working on Rust networking and concurrency systems for Lambda's chunk distribution plane.</span>
				<span class="about-item-title">2024</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="about-item-detail"><strong>Panoptyc</strong><br />AI R&D intern working on retail theft detection and low-latency IoT streaming infrastructure.</span>
				<span class="about-item-title">2024</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="about-item-detail"><strong>Spice Finance</strong><br />Quantitative developer on digital-asset valuation, lending, and capital-allocation systems.</span>
				<span class="about-item-title">2022</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="about-item-detail"><strong>New Jersey Institute of Technology</strong><br />AI research intern modeling fluid dynamics.</span>
				<span class="about-item-title">2019</span>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

